  "response": "Here are some potential downsides of owning a Porsche Panamera:\n\n1. High Initial Cost\n- Expensive purchase price\n- Significant upfront investment\n- Higher trim levels can cost over $200,000\n\n2. Maintenance Expenses\n- High maintenance and repair costs\n- Specialized parts are expensive\n- Servicing requires Porsche-certified mechanics\n\n3. Fuel Efficiency\n- Poor fuel economy, especially in performance models\n- High fuel consumption compared to other luxury sedans\n- Premium fuel required\n\n4. Depreciation\n- Rapid depreciation in first few years\n- High initial value drops quickly\n- Potential significant financial loss\n\n5. Practical Limitations\n- Limited rear passenger space\n- Smaller trunk compared to some luxury sedans\n- Complex interior design can be less user-friendly\n\n6. Insurance Costs\n- High insurance premiums\n- Expensive to insure due to vehicle's value\n- Higher risk classification\n\n7. Complexity\n- Advanced technology can be complicated\n- Potential electronic/system reliability issues\n- Expensive diagnostic and repair processes\n\n8. Ride Comfort\n- Stiffer suspension compared to traditional luxury sedans\n- Less comfortable on rough roads\n- Performance-oriented driving dynamics\n\nThese factors can vary depending on specific model and individual ownership experience.",
